results.name: Decimal expansion of Pi^4.
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..20000
formula: Pi^4 = 120 * Sum(j>=1, Sum(i=1..j-1, 1/(i*j)^2)). - _Enrique Pérez Herrero_, Jun 29 2012
program: (PARI) default(realprecision, 20080); x=Pi^4/10; for (n=2, 20000, d=floor(x); x=(x-d)*10; write("b092425.txt", n, " ", d)); \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Jun 22 2009
(MAGMA) R:=RealField(110); SetDefaultRealField(R); n:=Pi(R)^4; Reverse(Intseq(Floor(10^98*n))); // _Bruno Berselli_, Mar 12 2018
